Billy Leonard SKOOG v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 6038. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. March 25, 1959. Donald E. Kelley, U. S. Atty., and John S. Pfeiffer and Jack K. Anderson, Asst. U. S. Attys., Denver, Colo., for appellee.

Before MURRAH, LEWIS and BREITENSTEIN, Circuit Judges.

Affirmed without written opinion, for the reasons stated in the trial court’s memorandum opinion. D.C., 165 F.Supp. 397.
